> 
> Can someone take a look at their '78 Westy and count the number of
relay 
> boxes they have on the bottom of their fuse block?
> 
> I have space for one or two more relays. There is wiring there for at
least 
> one relay. I have not investigated what the color codes on the wires
this 
> week b/c I have not had the time. I know I can find the answer in
Bentley 
> but can anyone set me straight from memory?
> 
> I have two options on my bus I have not checked for operation yet. One
is 
> the rear window defroster. The other is that my bus is a Champagne
Edition 
> and it has factory intermittent wipers. Does this option use a relay
on the 
> fuse block? Is it the same relay as the blinker relay? Electrically it

> would work - the relay is a closed switch with opens once the load
heats 
> the contacts. The wipers would be the load and once the contacts open,
the 
> wipers would make one sweep and then park just like the driver had
turned 
> the wipers on and then off immediately in a basic bus without
intermittent 
> wipers.
> 
> Has anyone investigated adapting the Golf or Jetta or Passat
"programmable" 
> delay relay to the VW bus? I know it was discussed by one of the VW
lists 
> at one time. Basically you install this relay and based on a process 
> involving how you turn the wipers on and off, you can set the delay.
> 
> I know JC Whipme has generic delay kits but I am interested in the VW
version.
> 
> Thanks to any and all that can help.
